text: Stratford Central, a Telford Homes development, seen from Westfield Stratford City. Telford Homes is a house-building company that specialises in developments in non-prime areas of London. In April 2018 it was reported that Telford Homes was expecting record profits and revenues for the financial year 2017/18 as a result of London’s shortage of housing. In October 2019 Telford Homes was acquired by CBRE Group's real estate development subsidiary Trammell Crow Company in a £267m deal. ==References== == External links == Category:Home builders
